        <remarks>
          <para>Finds a matching FontScaleConverter for the given fontScale factor.
            
            Generally you shouldn't need this; you can use <c>android.util.TypedValue#applyDimension(int, float, DisplayMetrics)</c> directly and it will do
            the scaling conversion for you. Dimens and resources loaded from XML will also be
            automatically converted. But for UI frameworks or other situations where you need to do the
            conversion without an Android Context, you can use this method.</para>
